Required parameters : none

none

Encoding considerations :
quoted-printable - This media type is mostly ASCII characters but also
contains binary material. Quoted-printable is therefore the most
appropriate choice for transports that cannot handle binary material
directly.

Security considerations :
As with most application types this data is intended for interpretation by
a
program that understands the data on the recipient's system. Recipients
need
to understand that they are at the "mercy" of the sender, when receiving
this type of data, since data will be executed on their system, and the
security of their machines can be violated.

none

none
